{"title_page": "2013\u201314 Australian bushfire season", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=September 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2013}}\n{{Infobox wildfire\n|title=2013\u201314 Australian bushfire season\n|image=File:2013-14 Australian Bushfire season MODIS overview.png\n|caption = [[NASA]] [[MODIS]] burned area detections from June 2013 to May 2014\n|location= Australia\n|cost=\n|date= Winter (June) 2013 \u2013 Autumn (May) 2014\n|cause =\n|area= \n|fatalities = 4 total <br/>\n{{bulleted list |1 pilot contracted by the [[NSW Rural Fire Service]] (in accident) |3 other }} \n|injuries=\n|damage= \n|buildings= 571+ total <br/>\n{{bulleted list |371 houses |200+ non-residential structures }}\n|is_season =true\n|prev=2012\u201313 Australian bushfire season\n|next=2014\u201315 Australian bushfire season\n}}\n\nThe summer of 2013\u201314 was at the time, the most destructive bushfire season in terms of property loss since the [[2008\u201309 Australian bushfire season]], with the loss of 371 houses and several hundred non-residential buildings as a result of wild fires between 1 June 2015 and 31 May 2016. The season also suffered 4 fatalities; 2 died in [[New South Wales]], 1 in [[Western Australia]] and 1 in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]. One death was as a direct result of fire, 2 died due to unrelated health complications while fighting fires on their property, and a pilot contracted by the [[NSW Rural Fire Service]] died during an accident.\n\n== Climate summary and predictions ==\n\nThe season was predicted to have above average fire potential for most [[Australian state|states]] including portions of the north west of [[Western Australia]], the north west of the [[Northern Territory]] and large areas of central [[Queensland]] following below average rainfall and above average temperatures in these areas in the months leading up to the fire season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bushfirecrc.com/resources/firenote/northern-australia-seasonal-bushfire-outlook-2013|title=Northern Australian seasonal bushfire outlook 2013|year=2013|accessdate=7 September 2013|publisher=Bushfire CRC}}</ref> The year 2013 was the hottest on record in Australia, with the average temperature from September 2012 to August 2013 being calculated to be {{convert|22.9|C|F|0}} which is 1.1&nbsp;\u00b0C (1.6&nbsp;\u00b0F) higher than the 1961 to 1990 average.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.ninemsn.com.au/national/2013/09/03/18/16/australia-has-warmest-year-on-record-bom|title=Australia has warmest year on record: BoM|work=9 News|accessdate=3 September 2013|date=3 September 2013|publisher=[[Ninemsn]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017120429/http://news.ninemsn.com.au/national/2013/09/03/18/16/australia-has-warmest-year-on-record-bom|archive-date=17 October 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Fires of note==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" | State\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"12%\" align=\"center\" | Start date\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" | Deaths\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" | Injuries\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" | [[Residential area|Res.]] houses lost\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" | Other structures lost\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"8%\" align=\"center\" | Area ([[Hectare|ha]])\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"12%\" align=\"center\" | Local govt.\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" class=\"unsortable\" | Impacted communities\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" class=\"unsortable\" | Duration\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"6%\" align=\"center\" class=\"unsortable\" | Ref.\n|- style=\"height: 50px;\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[New South Wales|NSW]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <small>10 September 2013</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 7+\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | several\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 15