5tQE&t=278 |date=20 November 2015 |format=mp4 |medium=video |accessdate=16 May 2016 |author=.}}</ref><ref name=\"st-conspiracy\">{{cite news |title=Anti-vax mob full of jabber |work=[[The Sunday Telegraph (Sydney)]] |date=8 November 2015 |author=Hansen, Jane |url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/opinion/jane-hansen-antivax-mob-full-of-jabber/news-story/c537a883fc2983d22b22fd2b4f86424a |accessdate=16 May 2016}}</ref>\n|board_of_directors = (not disclosed)\n|registration_id = Y2079127-(NSW)<ref name=\"nswft-iar\">{{cite web |title=NSW Fair Trading: Incorporated Associations Register |url=http://associationspr.fairtrading.nsw.gov.au/Default.aspx |access-date=15 February 2016}}</ref> and ABN-30077002923<ref name=\"abr-abn\">{{cite web |title=ABR: Historical details for ABN 30 077 002 923 |url=http://abr.business.gov.au/SearchByAbnHistory.aspx?abn=30077002923 |access-date=15 February 2016|date=November 2014 }}</ref>\n|formerly = Australian Vaccination Network (AVN) 1994-2014,<ref name=\"abc-sceptical\" />  Australian Vaccination-Skeptics Network 2014-2018{{R|\"The Skeptic Zone 510\"}}\n|website = [http://avn.org.au/ AVN.org.au]\n|key_people = Tasha David, Brett Smith,<ref name=\"brett-smith-scd\">{{cite news |title=Anti-vaccine groups say they are pro-choice |work=[[Sunshine Coast Daily]] Qld. |dacriticised by doctors and other experts on immunisation.<ref name=HCCClateline/> The group has been called the \"stronghold of the anti-vaccination movement\" in Australia and is subject to widespread criticism from medical professionals, scientists and other proponents of vaccination.<ref name=\"smith\">{{cite news |title=Dick Smith criticises anti-vaccination 'm\n\nniversity of Wollongong]] researcher [[Judith Wilyman PhD isinformation' |work=[[ABC News (Australia)]] |date=7 August 2009 |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/08/07/2649266.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100507033715/http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/08/07/2649266.htm |archivedate